<p>Suppose I have the following DataFrame</p>  <pre><code>import pandas as pd import numpy as np df = pd.DataFrame({'col1': ['A', 'A', 'B', 'B'], 'col2':[1, 2, 3, 4],'col3':[5,6,7,8]})   """ In[3]:df Out[3]:    col1  col2  col3 0    A     1     5 1    A     2     6 2    B     3     7 3    B     4     8 """ </code></pre>  <p>I would like to group this data frame by col1 and find the dot product of col2 and col3 within each group. I know I can use the <code>.agg</code> method and the <code>np.dot</code> function but I am not sure how to pass col2 and col3 to the <code>np.dot</code> function:</p>  <pre><code>gb=df.groupby('col1')['col2','col3'].agg(np.dot(?,?)) </code></pre>  <p>I am looking for an output similar to this</p>  <pre><code>"""  col1    dot_prod A          1*5+2*6 B          3*7+4*8 """  </code></pre>